controller.interfaces

Interface IController

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Controller

    public interface IController
    Interface which define the Controller of the architectural pattern MVC, namely the operations usable by the IView on the IModel by reducing as much as possible the dependence between these two entities. It must be able to manage more than one IView at a time.

      • commandAdd

        void commandAdd(ISubject sub,
                int sem,
                Days d,
                Classrooms room,
                int hour,
                int n)
        It adds a subject in the timetable IModel.add(ISubject, int, Days, Classrooms, int, int). In case of unacceptable values in input, it informs the view of the error through the method IView.commandFailed(String).
        Parameters:
        sub - Subject to be added.
        sem - Semester in which the subject is scheduled.
        d - Day in which the subject must be inserted.
        room - Classroom in which the course will take place.
        hour - Subject’s starting time.
        n - Number of consecutive hours where the subject must be inserted.

      • commandRemove

        Parameters:
        sem - Semester in which a subject must be removed.
        d - Day in which the subject must be removed.
        room - Classroom in which the subject must be removed.
        hour - Hours to be removed.
        n - Number of consecutive hours to be removed.
